    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>American adaptations of late Sheraton-Style, open-backed side chairs. These are usually painted black with stencilled decoration that emulated gilt and lacquered furniture imported from Europe, and were developed and sold by Lambert Hitchcock in Connecticut in the mid-nineteenth century.</Note_Text>
